    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but those \"small moments\" don't really change the math of it. if we look at the universe as a whole, our presence is basically zero. if existence has no inherent value, then staying alive is just an arbitrary choice, right? it seems just as logical to stop existing as it does to keep going.",
